Rating: 4
This is a simple yet tastefully delicious recipe! My husband said it was very hearty, right up his alley. I did make a few changes though. I used my crockpot, as I knew the beans would soak up the sauce, and the chicken would be very, very tender. My changes are as follows: I did not use the chicken stock or salt at all. I did use diced chicken breast. I followed the directions exactly, cooking in a pot on the stove. Then I transferred to the crockpot. I set the pot at low. After about two hours, I tasted it and thought it needed a little something. So, I added liquid smoke (Colgins), about 2 teaspoons, and I did add four more pieces of chopped cooked bacon. The stew was very thick, and some might want to add a little broth at the end of cooking. I did not, as I love thick sauces. Oh, and I did add two chicken boullion cubes also, for a little more flavor, as I added no salt at all. The stew turned out flavorful, after about 5 hours in the crockpot. The chicken fell apart. The flavor was to die for. Everyone must try this recipe. I do believe the crockpot improved the flavor quite a bit because of the long cooking time. This is a keeper! Oh, and I will definitely double this one because we did not have any leftovers, and I wish we did!

