This is a lovely, comforting, full flavor dish. I've made it twice, both times with rave reviews from a tough crowd of food freaks. Use high quality bacon, as it serves as the hidden base for everything that follows. First time I used chicken breasts with skin on, second time boned thighs, skin off. Both ways were great. Also, I cut up chicken after sauteing into bit size pieces. I followed the advice of another reviewer and added the basil just before serving. Takes about two and one-half hours to double the recipe, enough for sixteen mean hungry people as a main dish. Great.

