This dish was very easy & reasonably quick to prepare. The finished stew looked appetising & comforting. I'd give it 2 1/2 forks if I could ! The down-side of the relatively quick cooking time was that the dried oregano still had that harsh & rather overpowering taste that dried herbs can have (& I actually halved the amount called for in the recipe as I don't really like dried herbs) if they don't cook for long enough. Ditto the canned tomatoes. I would make this again but only for quick, mid-week family meals. It just doesn't do it for me for company or for when you want something a little more sophisticated.

Rating: 4
