This recipe is just wonderful! It got rave reviews from my family and is now on our regular weekly menu. I served it over mashed potatoes, but it would be probably be good with rice or noodles too. I left out the bacon (didn't have any in the house), replaced the tomatoes with 1 large can of "Crushed tomatoes with puree" (because I did have it in the house) which worked out great, added a couple of carrots with the onions and garlic, and substituted Herbs de Provence, but basil and oregano would work well too. Serve up some steamed green veggies too for some added nutrition and color variation.

